    "name": "Text (Anthem 1)",
    "liturgy_name": "Good Friday",
    "liturgy_slug": "good_friday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "We glory in your cross, O Lord, and praise and glorify your holy resurrection; for by virtue of your cross joy has come to the whole world. May God be merciful to us and bless us, show us the light of his countenance, and come to us. Let your ways be known upon earth, your saving health among all nations. Let the peoples praise you, O God; let all the peoples praise you. We glory in your cross, O Lord, and praise and glorify your holy resurrection; for by virtue of your cross joy has come to the whole world.",
    "section": "Anthem 1",
    "source_file": "friday.html",
    "page_number": 280,
